# Plan: Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js already has `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (in `src/models.js`) supporting
multimodal VLMs like Florence-2, LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, PaliGemma, etc. However, there is no
`pipeline("image-text-to-text", ...)` entry point. This plan adds that pipeline so users
can pass an image and a text prompt and receive generated text in return — covering tasks
like visual Q&A, image captioning with instructions, OCR, and scene understanding.

---

## Critical File

**`src/pipelines.js`** — the only file that needs to change.

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Add import for `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (line ~44)

In the existing `import { ... } from './models.js'` block (lines 21–45), add
`AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the list, after `AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction`:

```javascript
// Before (line 43-44):
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    PreTrainedModel,

// After:
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,
    PreTrainedModel,
```

---

### Step 2 — Add the new pipeline class (insert after line 2005, after `ImageToTextPipeline`)

Insert the full block between the closing `}` of `ImageToTextPipeline` (line 2005) and
the `/**` comment that opens `ImageClassificationPipeline` (line 2007):

```javascript
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Generate text conditioned on an image and a text prompt.
 * @param {ImageInput} image The input image.
 * @param {string} text The text prompt that describes what to do with the image.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput>} An array of objects containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */

/**
 * Image-text-to-text pipeline using any `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline generates
 * text conditioned on an image and a text prompt. It can be used for visual question answering,
 * image captioning with instructions, and other vision-language tasks.
 *
 * **Example:** Describe an image using `onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft');
 * const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const output = await pipe(url, '<DETAILED_CAPTION>');
 * // [{ generated_text: 'Two cats are resting comfortably on a couch ...' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(image, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {

        // Preprocess image
        const preparedImage = (await prepareImages(image))[0];
        const { pixel_values } = await this.processor(preparedImage);

        // Tokenize text prompt
        const { input_ids, attention_mask } = this.tokenizer(text, {
            padding: true,
            truncation: true,
        });

        // Run model
        const output = await this.model.generate({
            inputs: input_ids,
            pixel_values,
            attention_mask,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        });

        // Decode output
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(/** @type {Tensor} */(output), {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        }).map(x => ({ generated_text: x.trim() }));

        return decoded;
    }
}
```

**Design notes:**
- Uses `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` (has both `tokenizer` and `processor`), exactly
  like `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` and `ImageToTextPipeline`.
- `inputs: input_ids` — the text prompt is the primary generation driver; `pixel_values`
  is passed as a kwarg. This matches `imageTextToTextForward` / `genericTextToTextForward`
  in `src/models.js` which expect `input_ids` as the text tensor and `pixel_values` as
  the visual modality kwarg.
- Non-batched (single image + single prompt) to keep the interface simple; matches the
  `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` precedent for multimodal generation pipelines.
- `batch_decode` with `skip_special_tokens: true` follows `ImageToTextPipeline`.

---

### Step 3 — Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS` (insert after the `"image-to-text"` entry, ~line 3255)

After the closing `},` of the `"image-to-text"` entry (line 3255), add:

```javascript
    "image-text-to-text": {
        "tokenizer": AutoTokenizer,
        "pipeline": ImageTextToTextPipeline,
        "model": AutoModelForImageTextToText,
        "processor": AutoProcessor,
        "default": {
            "model": "onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft",
        },
        "type": "multimodal",
    },
```

---

### Step 4 — Add to factory function JSDoc list (~line 3427)

In the `pipeline()` JSDoc `@param {T} task` bullet list, add alphabetically after the
`"image-to-text"` line:

```javascript
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
```

So the block becomes:
```javascript
 *  - `"image-to-text"`: will return a `ImageToTextPipeline`.
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
 *  - `"object-detection"`: will return a `ObjectDetectionPipeline`.
```

---

## Summary of All Edits

| # | Location in `src/pipelines.js` | Change |
|---|-------------------------------|--------|
| 1 | Line ~44 (models import block) | Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to import list |
| 2 | After line 2005 (after `ImageToTextPipeline` class) | Insert new typedef block + `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class |
| 3 | After line 3255 (after `"image-to-text"` in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`) | Insert `"image-text-to-text"` task entry |
| 4 | Line ~3427 (factory function JSDoc) | Add `"image-text-to-text"` bullet |

